What happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?

	The folder beomes the repository. to designate the folder and a place to store the data.

How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository? What value do you think it offers?

	The staging area only includes files added manually.
	Only files in the staging area can be commited.
	Prevents accidental commits. Every commit is deliberate.
	Easier to keep track of files to be commited.

How can you use the staging area to make sure you have one commit per logical change?

	Only add files that working with each other.

What are some situations when branches would be helpful in keeping your history organized? How would branches help?

	Work on experimental code.
	Converting to a different language.
	Texting different layouts.
	In every Way.

How do the diagrams help you visualize the branch structure?

	Helps to see how each everything connects to each other.

What is the result of merging two branches together? Why do we represent it in the diagram the way we do?

	Combines all changes since each branch was made.
	To depict the cumulative change from each branch.

